# FORT-6 (P2 Codex audit) + FORT-6 followup (broken-build fix):
# env-style files are ignored by default. The repo allows ONE exception:
# `.env` may contain ONLY non-secret, build-time public values
# (Supabase URL, publishable/anon key, project id, the public Stripe
# publishable token). Vite needs these at build time to embed them in
# the client bundle — without them the deployed app crashes on
# hydration with "Missing Supabase environment variable(s)".
#
# What MUST go elsewhere (operator secrets):
#   - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY → Lovable / Cloudflare Worker env vars
#   - GUARDIAN_SECRET → Supabase function secrets
#   - Stripe restricted / secret keys → Lovable env vars
#   - Anthropic API keys, AI provider keys → server-side env only
#   - any *_SECRET, *_TOKEN that isn't a publishable token
#
# Anything matching .env.local / .env.production / .env.development
# stays ignored to discourage that pattern (Vite reads .env for all
# environments unless overridden).
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

